Roscosmos chief Dmitry Rogozin said the "world's most powerful" missile is being equipped for "new tests". So far, the only test of the missile was in April from the Plesetsk Cosmodrome in northern Russia. Rogozin previously warned the weapons would be commissioned no later than autumn, saying it is "on schedule" The 208-ton, 15,880mph weapon is about the size of a 14-storey tower block. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 